ust as Germany has dragged away Frenchmen, Poles, Czechs, and they do repatriate them to their countries, so do we want [to go] to our own country. Only there is our country."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3939.945","u": "But.,"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "3940.533","u": "For this reason, for instance, I understand that for England we are considered &#39;illegal&#39;."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3944.950","u": "Oh!"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "3945.221","u": "But I shall enter my country legally. I do not come to take away [anything] from anybody. I come only to help, build, work. I am, thanks God, still well. I can work."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3957.312","u": "And what do you think . . . , How long will you still remain here, now . . . ?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "3960.553","u": "It is not a question, how long. As long as it may be&#226;the final goal is the Land of Israel. We have not put up any stipulations, and we do not make stipulations to the Land of Israel. Since it means [to come to] good conditions, I do not set any fixed date when to get there."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3975.176","u": "Now let us see. It is being said that the UNNRA will be terminated in six, seven months. What then?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "3981.478","u": "So what: The UNNRA will terminate, we don&#39;t care! We have gone through the gravest moments. For us there is no worry what will happen tomorrow. The horror against hunger we have no more. We have a greater horror, that we may now . . . we had now a chance to be set free, and if we should lose the freedom, then life is not worth anything. It is purposeless, and purposeless is any struggle to live without freedom."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4008.809","u": "And what do people do here all day?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4010.965","u": "We learn &#39;Kikhot&#39;, we learn Hebrew."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4015.563","u": "What is &#39;Kikhot?&#39;"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4016.392","u": "That means discussions. People discuss Jewish history, Zionist history, world history, we learn."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4021.337","u": "Hm . . . And . . ."},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4025.061","u": "And the time passes. We sing, we tell each other experiences [?] of the lagers. Because everyone has experiences to tell."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4034.272","u": "Do you work in any way? Do you learn a trade?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4036.141","u": "Here there is no trade school."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4039.247","u": "Why? Couldn&#39;t you bring in the ORT?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4040.860","u": "I don&#39;t know."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4042.488","u": "Did you request that trade schools be installed?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4045.533","u": "Here in Italy the Hachsharas,in general, are not organized as the ones in Germany. In Germany, for instance, there were agricultural Hachsharas and trade school Hachshara. Here we have come not to stay, here we have come to get away as soon as possible. We wanted to go straight ahead, to get to our final goal. But unfortunately, due to the occurrence of various obstacles [?] we had to remain. And we believe the time shall not be a long one."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4076.715","u": "There are now here a few people from the Land of Israel. What are they doing?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4083.544","u": "Those people? They tell us about the life in the Land of Israel, they teach, they teach Hebrew, they lead discussions, Jewish history . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4094.760","u": "Now, are there families in this place?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4097.293","u": "Here are families too. That means, the newly created families."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4101.861","u": "Aha . . . And where are all these small children from?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4104.620","u": "Those are all those who were born right after the liberation."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4110.153","u": "Oh! But there are here also children who are three, four years old."},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4112.520","u": "Oh! Those are older children who were in camps for internees, or from the Rumanian and Hungarian communities who were in the Ghetto. Because not all Rumanian and Hungarian Jews were led out."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4124.776","u": "Oh!, and they arrived now?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4125.982","u": "They have come now. Because the situation is there, too, a very tense one."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4129.962","u": "Aha . . . Are these all people who have come from Poland already after . . . , after the war?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4135.600","u": "Yes, of course. All have come after the war."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4138.980","u": "Yes. But do people leave Poland now?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4140.623","u": "Oh! Just lately! No, there are none here who have left lately."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4144.814","u": "Ah . . ."},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4145.236","u": "But now we know that large masses of Jews are fleeing on account of the pogroms which now take place in Poland. And about Italy letting them in [the last sentence was possibly said with irony]"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4154.402","u": "Did you hear that there are some Christians who came together with the Jews?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4159.256","u": "There are no Christians . . . Yes, there are Christians, there are Italians . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4162.784","u": "In this place?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4163.922","u": "Here, exactly, no. But there are Italians who have intermarried with Jews."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4167.796","u": "Aha . . . And they are being accepted?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4170.208","u": "Oh, Yes! They are accepted. And there are also Russian women, and there are Polish women who have been hiding Jews. They hid them. And the Jews have married them."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4177.957","u": "And they go . . . ?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4179.917","u": "Yes, they got to the Land of Israel. They learn now[?] Hebrew."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4183.882","u": "Yes. Do you have here Jewish teachers? Do you have a Rabbi here?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4187.123","u": "No. Here we have no Rabbi."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4188.751","u": "And they are here not very Orthodox?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4190.591","u": "No, here they are not . . . there is a block of about sixty people . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4194.013","u": "Here?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4194.586","u": ". . . who eat a . . . , have a separate chef and eat Kosher."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4199.606","u": "Aha . . . , but the others don&#39;t?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4201.385","u": "The others do not. The others cannot afford it."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4204.475","u": "How come they cannot afford . . . ?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4206.224","u": "Because there are no facilities. And there are many who do not like to watch out for it [??]. They say that if they should come to a permanent [?] place, to the Land of Israel, they shall behave again as they once used to behave at home."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4215.661","u": "Now tell me, in the lagers, what were the pious Jews doing, when they were . . . ?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4219.099","u": "When, in the times of the KZ&#39;s?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4221.526","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4222.189","u": "In the times of the KZ&#39;s, for instance . . . , I happen to be a Jew who prays [observes regular prayertime]"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4225.928","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4226.200","u": "So once they found on me a little prayer book [in Hebrew]. So I was given fifty strokes and a kick."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4231.853","u": "For that?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4232.456","u": "Yes, for that. For that reason one would have to watch himself. And so I first prayed for a time from memory."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4240.084","u": "Aha . . ."},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4240.898","u": ". . . but God have mercy if one was caught."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4243.612","u": "And on Yom Kippur [Day of Atonement] or Rosh Hashana [New Year&#39;s]?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4245.301","u": "On Yom Kippur there was just nothing. It could happen that on Yom Kippur they would assign us to the worst labor. When they knew that there was a special [Sacred] Day they plagued [us] especially, still more."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4254.030","u": "They would not allow to pray?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4255.703","u": "Oh!, prayer and such things were out of the question."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4258.839","u": "Well, the Jews took with them their phylacteries, their prayer shawls."},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4261.794","u": "Whatever they took with them [of a religious nature] was all burned."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4266.603","u": "Now what else did you want to tell me? [a whisper] Well, I think we shall conclude."},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4273.568","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4274.246","u": "[In English] This concludes Spool 94. This concludes number 94."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4281.312","u": "[In German] Have you any relatives in America?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4283.322","u": "Yes, sure."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4284.112","u": "Do you have the addresses?"},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4285.047","u": "I don&#39;t have the addresses."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4286.253","u": "Aha . . . [In English] This concludes spool number 94, taken at Tradate, near Como and Milano. Mr. Schoer . . . Shw . . ."},    {"who": "Jacob Schwarzfitter", "start": "4298.012","u": "Schwarzfitter"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "4298.555","u": ". . . Schwarzfitter reporting. Recording of Illinois Institute of Technology. 125 volts, 50 kilo&#226; 50 cycles."}        ]
